race.comment: HOPE'S ZONE (4) is a sprinter who excels over the short dashes. Was too tough when scoring last time over 352m at this track in a Free For All (19.62). Has a good record here at this journey including three wins. Strong form has emerged from her last run. Can make it two on the bounce. OUT OF AUSTRIAN (5) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (20.06) at this track behind WHO'S THE MAN in a Free For All. Chased the leaders and with a clean run can be prominent. Bold showing expected. SHE'S A LADETTE (1) is a handy type who was well below best latest at Q Straight, finishing seventh (19.28) in a Grade 5. Generally fast into stride but was shuffled back from the tricky draw last time. Goes very well from this draw with two wins and two minor placings from five starts. Has ability and can measure up. MILO DAVIS (3) must be respected at his pet track and distance.
